ZCZC EE03
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 232300 UTC
ON SATURDAY SLACK AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED IN THE N SEA
WITH SHALLOW LOW CENTRED N OF THE UK AND A SLACK FLOW ACROSS NITON. HIGH
PRESSURE SINKS SE DURING SUNDAY WITH WEAK RIDGE EXTENDING N IN THE ATLANTIC
FM THE AZORES AND TOWARDS AN ANTICYCLONE CENTRED NEAR ICELAND. A FURTHER
SHALLOW LOW WILL BE CENTRED BISCAY. A SLACK CYCLONIC FLOW THEN DEVELOPS ACROSS
THE UK WITH SHALLOW CENTRES LIKELY NEAR THE UK AND W OF SHANNON. HOWEVER
CONFIDENCE IN DETAILS IS LOW BY THIS STAGE. THIS CYCLONIC REGION PERSISTS
DURING TUESDAY WITH SHALLOW LOW CENTRES GRADUALLY DPN AND WERNMOST CENTRE
MOV E INTO W NITON. NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP BUT THESE STRENGTHENING TUESDAY
WITH STRG WINDS PERHAPS NEAR GALES S OF THE WERN LOW. AREAS OF WIDESPREAD
FOG ALSO POSS IN THE SW APPROACHES OVERNIGHT FRIDAY INTO SATURDAY AND THEN
LUNDY FASTNET AND IRISH SEA OVERNIGHT INTO SUNDAY.
